(1409, 1, '2022-04-24 07:49:16', '2022-04-24 07:49:16', '<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"about-the-global-green-recovery-collaborative\"><strong>About the Global Green Recovery Collaborative</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GGRC was founded by an all volunteer global team of University of Cambridge Conservation Leadership masters alumni at the onset of the Covid-19 pandemic. With so many lives lost and economies shattered, many have asked, “How do we recover from this?” We believe that the best solution is to collaborate for a green recovery in order to achieve an environmentally resilient, just, and equitable future. With the help of our website development team, we launched this platform to enable action and collaboration for a green recovery not just from Covid-19, but from all environmental challenges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is our hope that this collaborative will inspire people to act and share knowledge, tools and opportunities to work collectively, so we will all succeed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"what-is-a-green-recovery\">What is a “green recovery”?</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Green Recovery is the big redesign! It is repairing our world and recovering from environmental damage, to become healthy and resilient.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Green recovery is also the process of transforming how we live and interact with each other and our environment so that biodiversity will thrive, the climate will stabilize, and we will be able to adapt to new realities that have resulted from past ways of living. As social and environmental injustices and harms are linked, green recovery is a response to the complex, interconnected woes that affect people and the planet in an urgent mission for a better future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2022-04-24 08:18:28', '2022-04-24 08:18:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ggrc_website/?page_id=1409', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(1410, 1, '2022-04-24 07:49:16', '2022-04-24 07:49:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Global Green Recovery Collaborative (GGRC) gets people talking, sharing information, and acting together in order to implement transformative solutions for our planet’s future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GGRC was founded by a team of University of Cambridge Conservation Leadership masters alumni in the midst of the Covid-19 pandemic. The advent of the pandemic made it clear that we need an environmentally resilient, just, and equitable future. Though Covid-19 seemed to appear out of nowhere, it is rooted in ecological devastation, and since countries across the globe were so unprepared, it has and continues to wreak major damage. With so many lives lost and economies shattered, many are asking, “How do we recover from this?”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"what-is-a-green-recovery\">What is a “green recovery”?</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We think of Green Recovery as the big redesign! It is the action of repairing our world and recovering from environmental damage, to become healthy and resilient.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Green recovery is also the process of transforming how people live and interact with each other and our environment so that biodiversity will thrive, the climate will stabilize, and people and wildlife will be able to adapt to new realities that have resulted from past ways of living.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Green recovery, at present, includes a response to the Covid-19 pandemic, but it is not limited by the pandemic. As social and environmental injustices and harms are linked, green recovery is a response to the full complexity of interconnected woes that affect people and the planet in an urgent mission for a better future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1409-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-04-24 07:49:16', '2022-04-24 07:49:16', '', 1409, 'http://localhost/ggrc_website/?p=1410', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
